Take a look at ProcessResult and ProcessStatus; returning a FINISH from 
one Processor should cause a skip-forward to the first Processor that 
self-identifies as a post-processor. There&#39;s also a facility to JUMP 
(fast-forward, really) via this return value to another Processor by the 
target Processor&#39;s String key name, though that facility has seen so 
little use there might be issues with it.

The 2.0 precedence functionality offers a lot of control of URI/queue 
ordering, but be careful of the performance costs of complicated 
policies: in a large crawl, expressing very fine-grained preference of 
URI ordering means lots of essentially random-access queue inserts, and 
then random-access disk seeks.

- Gordon @ IA

